Hoje como ontem, estas "Máquinas Voadoras" continuam a surpreender-nos, capazes de viajar de um universo para outro, realizando as mais insólitas manobras, sobrevoando qualquer espaço aéreo, mudando a sua trajetória subitamente, suspendendo-se por horas à vontade, esses Artefatos que fazem parte do chamado Fenômeno Ovni, deixaram o registro do seu presença por mais de sete décadas ininterruptas, é hora de aceitar esta irrefutável realidade extraterrestre... the 
  BLACK PHONE 

The first horror film I have enjoyed in a long while, mainly because it was not necessarily a horror movie, more a supernatural serial killer film.
There was lots to like about the black phone, I thought the 70’s vibe was spot on and though the story was very simple it made for a tense watch.
The acting was very good, Ethan hawke was very  impressive  in his role, but for me the brother and sister carried the film,especially the boy who was in pretty much every scene. The film had a few supernatural scenes but It was the real part of the story that shone through.
I found myself caring about the 2 main  characters and that led to the ending feeling very satisfying and a little emotional.
The only thing lacking for me was maybe a bit of a back story for Ethan hawke’s character.
I enjoyed though and would recommend for horror and non horror fans.

Clip: The Black Phone (2021)

Theaters: June 24th

Finney Shaw is abducted by a man in a strange mask and kept in a sound-proof basement. A disconnected phone on the wall begins to ring. The callers on the other end are previous victims of the strange man. They intend to make sure Finney doesn’t become the next victim.

The Black Phone was written by Scott Derrickson and C. Robert Cargill, based off the short story by Joe Hill. Derrickson also directed. Ethan Hawke, Jeremy Davies, James Ransone, Madeleine McGraw, and Mason Thames star.

BLACK PHONE es una película oscura e intensa con elementos sobrenaturales y reales que te mantienen al borde del asiento. Las actuaciones de MASON THAMES y MADELEINE McGRAW son acertadas y ambos mostraron una química innegable en cámara. Igualmente, el actor Ethan Hawke logra interpretar a un personaje malévolo, y lo hace magistralmente. Los elementos visuales y la banda sonora son claves elevando la intensidad y, sobretodo, el terror y la tensión en la historia.
